<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In graphics, any smooth progression from one color or gray value to another, usually comprising a series of steps which, ideally, should be imperceptible. In digital output, one particular defect of gradients is <a title="Banding" href="Banding">banding</a>, or the visibility of the discrete steps of a gradient, usually produced when the system or output device cannot generate enough gray or color levels to render a smooth gradient. 
</p>
